"title": "6728: regeneration",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6728",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The radical renewal of a person's inner being by the work of God's Spirit.</p>\n<h2>The need for regeneration</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:3\">JHN 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1\">EPH 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:5\">EPH 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13\">COL 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>Regeneration is a work of God</h2>\n<h3>It originates in God the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>Regeneration cannot be controlled by human actions or rituals; it is an act of God's sovereign will.</em></p>\n<h3>It is made possible by the resurrection of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3\">1PE 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>It occurs through the hearing of the Christian gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:18\">JAS 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:23-1Pet1:25\">1PE 1:23–1:25</a> <em>The “word of God” is the good news about Jesus Christ.</em></p>\n<h3>It is effected by God's Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5-John3:8\">JHN 3:5–3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:63\">JHN 6:63</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Regeneration is given to those who believe in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:1\">1JN 5:1</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Baptism is the sign of regeneration</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5\">JHN 3:5</a></strong> <em>Water here is seen by some, though not all, interpreters as a reference to baptism, administered by the church to new converts as a sign of their new birth and their entry into the Christian community.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38-Acts2:39\">ACT 2:38–2:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:26\">EPH 5:25–5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:5\">TIT 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>The results of regeneration</h2>\n<h3>Entry into God's kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:5\">JHN 3:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>A new holiness of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:9\">1JN 3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:18\">1JN 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:1-1Pet2:2\">1PE 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>Love for other people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:7\">1JN 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:2\">1JN 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Victory over the world's sinful pattern of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:4\">1JN 5:4</a></strong></p>",
